### Multiplying and reducing to lowest terms

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\dfrac{-3x+21}{-2x-4}\cdot\dfrac{x^2-16}{x-7}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-3(x-7)}{-2(x+2)}\cdot\dfrac{(x+4)(x-4)}{x-7}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{\cancel{-1}\cdot 3\cancel{(x-7)}(x+4)(x-4)}{\cancel{-1}\cdot 2(x+2)\cancel{(x-7)}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{3(x+4)(x-4)}{2(x+2)}
\end{align}$

### Multiplying and reducing to lowest terms

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\dfrac{-4x-32}{x^2-12x+36}\cdot\dfrac{x^2-9x+18}{3x+24}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-4(x+8)}{(x-6)^2}\cdot\dfrac{(x-6)(x-3)}{3(x+8)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-4\cancel{(x+8)}\cancel{(x-6)}(x-3)}{3\cancel{(x-6)}(x-6)\cancel{(x+8)}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-4(x-3)}{3(x-6)}
\end{align}$

### Multiplying and reducing to lowest terms

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\dfrac{x^2+8x+15}{-5x-5}\cdot\dfrac{x^2+2x+1}{2x+10}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{(x+3)(x+5)}{-5(x+1)}\cdot\dfrac{(x+1)^2}{2(x+5)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{(x+3)\cancel{(x+5)}\cancel{(x+1)}(x+1)}{-10\cancel{(x+1)}\cancel{(x+5)}}
\\\\
&=-\dfrac{(x+3)(x+1)}{10}
\end{align}$

### Multiplying and reducing to lowest terms

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\dfrac{5x-10}{x^2-36}\cdot\dfrac{4x+24}{x^2+5x-14}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{5(x-2)}{(x+6)(x-6)}\cdot\dfrac{4(x+6)}{(x-2)(x+7)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{20\cancel{(x-2)}\cancel{(x+6)}}{\cancel{(x+6)}(x-6)\cancel{(x-2)}(x+7)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{20}{(x-6)(x+7)}
\end{align}$

### Multiplying and reducing to lowest terms

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\dfrac{x^2+5x+4}{x^2-13x+40}\cdot\dfrac{x-8}{x^2-1}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{(x+1)(x+4)}{(x-5)(x-8)}\cdot\dfrac{x-8}{(x+1)(x-1)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{\cancel{(x+1)}(x+4)\cancel{(x-8)}}{(x-5)\cancel{(x-8)}\cancel{(x+1)}(x-1)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{x+4}{(x-5)(x-1)}
\end{align}$

### Multiplying and reducing to lowest terms

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\dfrac{x+2}{x^2+14x+49}\cdot\dfrac{x^2+6x-7}{x^2+x-2}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{x+2}{(x+7)^2}\cdot\dfrac{(x+7)(x-1)}{(x+2)(x-1)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{\cancel{(x+2)}\cancel{(x+7)}\cancel{(x-1)}}{(x+7)\cancel{(x+7)}\cancel{(x+2)}\cancel{(x-1)}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{1}{x+7}
\end{align}$

### Multiplying and reducing to lowest terms

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\dfrac{x-7}{-5x+40}\cdot\dfrac{x^2-64}{-4x+28}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{x-7}{-5(x-8)}\cdot\dfrac{(x+8)(x-8)}{-4(x-7)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{\cancel{(x-7)}(x+8)\cancel{(x-8)}}{20\cancel{(x-8)}\cancel{(x-7)}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{x+8}{20}
\end{align}$

### Dividing and reducing to lowest terms

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\dfrac{\,\,\,\dfrac{x^2-3x-10}{x-3}\,\,\,}{\dfrac{x+2}{3x-9}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{\,\,\,\dfrac{(x+2)(x-5)}{x-3}\,\,\,}{\dfrac{x+2}{3(x-3)}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{(x+2)(x-5)}{x-3}\cdot\dfrac{3(x-3)}{x+2}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{\cancel{(x+2)}(x-5)\cdot 3\cancel{(x-3)}}{\cancel{(x-3)}\cancel{(x+2)}}
\\\\
&=3(x-5)
\end{align}$

### Dividing and reducing to lowest terms

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\dfrac{\,\,\,\dfrac{x^2-8x+16}{x^2+4x-21}\,\,\,}{\dfrac{-2x+8}{x+7}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{\,\,\,\dfrac{(x-4)^2}{(x+7)(x-3)}\,\,\,}{\dfrac{-2(x-4)}{x+7}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{(x-4)^2}{(x+7)(x-3)}\cdot\dfrac{x+7}{-2(x-4)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{(x-4)\cancel{(x-4)}\cancel{(x+7)}}{-2\cancel{(x+7)}(x-3)\cancel{(x-4)}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{x-4}{-2(x-3)}
\end{align}$

### Dividing and reducing to lowest terms

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\dfrac{\,\,\,\dfrac{4x-24}{-3x-15}\,\,\,}{\dfrac{x^2-36}{x+5}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{\,\,\,\dfrac{4(x-6)}{-3(x+5)}\,\,\,}{\dfrac{(x+6)(x-6)}{x+5}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{4(x-6)}{-3(x+5)}\cdot\dfrac{x+5}{(x+6)(x-6)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{4\cancel{(x-6)}\cancel{(x+5)}}{-3\cancel{(x+5)}(x+6)\cancel{(x-6)}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{4}{-3(x+6)}
\end{align}$

### Dividing and reducing to lowest terms

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\dfrac{\dfrac{x+8}{x^2-6x-7}}{\,\,\,\dfrac{x^2+16x+64}{x+1}\,\,\,}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{\,\,\,\dfrac{x+8}{(x+1)(x-7)}\,\,\,}{\dfrac{(x+8)^2}{x+1}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{x+8}{(x+1)(x-7)}\cdot\dfrac{x+1}{(x+8)^2}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{\cancel{(x+8)}\cancel{(x+1)}}{\cancel{(x+1)}(x-7)\cancel{(x+8)}(x+8)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{1}{(x-7)(x+8)}
\end{align}$

### Dividing and reducing to lowest terms

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\dfrac{x^2-16}{x-2}\div\dfrac{x^2+3x-4}{x-8}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{(x+4)(x-4)}{x-2}\div\dfrac{(x-1)(x+4)}{x-8}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{(x+4)(x-4)}{x-2}\cdot\dfrac{x-8}{(x-1)(x+4)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{\cancel{(x+4)}(x-4)(x-8)}{(x-2)(x-1)\cancel{(x+4)}}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{(x-4)(x-8)}{(x-2)(x-1)}
\end{align}$

### Dividing and reducing to lowest terms

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\dfrac{x^2+10x+25}{x-5}\div\dfrac{x^2-25}{5x+10}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{(x+5)^2}{x-5}\div\dfrac{(x+5)(x-5)}{5(x+2)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{(x+5)^2}{x-5}\cdot\dfrac{5(x+2)}{(x+5)(x-5)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{5\cancel{(x+5)}(x+5)(x+2)}{(x-5)\cancel{(x+5)}(x-5)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{5(x+5)(x+2)}{(x-5)^2}
\end{align}$

### Dividing and reducing to lowest terms

$\begin{align}
&\phantom{=}\dfrac{-4x-12}{x-7}\div\dfrac{x^2-12x+36}{2x-14}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-4(x+3)}{x-7}\div\dfrac{(x-6)^2}{2(x-7)}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-4(x+3)}{x-7}\cdot\dfrac{2(x-7)}{(x-6)^2}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-8(x+3)\cancel{(x-7)}}{\cancel{(x-7)}(x-6)^2}
\\\\
&=\dfrac{-8(x+3)}{(x-6)^2}
\end{align}$
